Hi everyone! Here's my Analog Arrays project. Onces every second, it randomly selects a PWM pin and writes a random value to it. If it was already on, it turns it off. A tip I'd give for this project is to only put what's necessary inside the If...else statement. I first reassigned my state tracker and added delay inside the if...else but ultimately found it to be more efficient to put them outside. 

